---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description: "About Shameer Baramy. Backend, platform engineering, distributed systems, AI agents, and tools for thought.",
	title: "About",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<section>
		<h1 class="heading-1">About</h1>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				I'm Shameer, a backend and platform engineer.
			</p>
			<p>
				Most of my work is on backend services, distributed systems, and the
				internal tools other engineers use every day. I mostly write Go and
				Python, with some TypeScript and Rust.
			</p>
			<p>
				A lot of it comes down to developer productivity: building the
				platforms and tools that help engineering teams move faster and make
				better use of their time.
			</p>
			<p>
				I write here about platform engineering, developer productivity, LLM
				agents, distributed systems, and note-taking.
			</p>
			<p>
				A few things I've built are on the <a href="/projects/">projects</a> page.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</PageLayout>
